From: Claude <claude.ai.2026@simonlaux.de>
Date: Mon, 20 Jul 2026 16:56:05 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 55/58] web-app: two-pane settings layout on wide viewports

On viewports >=800px the settings dialog becomes a single 720px
Discord/macOS-style two-pane dialog: the navigation list (profile,
sections, connectivity, donate/help/about) is the left sidebar and the
selected section renders in a pane on the right, no stacked section
dialogs. Below 800px everything keeps the existing stacked-dialog flow,
including fullscreen-on-mobile.

The nav list and the per-section bodies are extracted into shared
SettingsNav/SettingsSectionBody components so both layouts render the
exact same content; SettingsIconButton gains an 'active' highlight
(aria-current) for the sidebar.
